- New feature: DROP TABLE statement
- Fix: Various database engine stability fixes
- Fix: Multiple fixes and improvements in the database export output
- Fix: POST request returns code 201 on success
- Fix: CentOS/RHEL 8 build procedure for the Protobuf updated to produce
  static librararies

2020-10-14 version 0.8.0

- New feature: Database export functionality in the siocli
- New feature: User authentication with token
- New feature: User token management statements
- New feature: REST Server
- New feature: Use master key to encrypt individual database keys
- New feature: Database schema version
- New feature: New configuration option for limiting maximum number of databases
- New feature: New configuration option for limiting maximum number of tables
- Change: Removed configuration options for database and table cache sizes
- Fix: Database encryption key removed from table SYS_DATABASES
- Fix: Multiple stability fixes
- Build: Build instructions for Ubuntu 20.04 LTS
- Build: Build instructions for Debian 10
- Installation: Standartized locations of the 3rd party libraries
- Thirdparty: Upgrade to protobuf-3.12.3
- Thirdparty: Upgrade to ut8cpp-3.1.1

